<li>Be able to manage and coordinate\u00a0 events (Workshops, training, and public events )<\/li><li>Understand Social Media platforms and digital media strategy.\u00a0<\/li><li>Be willing to learn new skills<\/li><li>Be self-driven and diligent\u00a0<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>As the <strong>Communications Intern, <\/strong>you will work closely with our team to communicate the organization\u2019s work to beneficiaries and partners, this will include but not limited to&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Conducting interviews with beneficiaries and project participants&nbsp;<\/li><li>Managing Social Media Accounts (Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, and YouTube )<\/li><li>Data gathering and analysis&nbsp;<\/li><li>Attending events and public functions on behalf of the organization&nbsp;<\/li><li>&nbsp;Writing&nbsp; blog posts and press releases&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Monitor online reactions to&nbsp; <strong>Defy Hate Now\u2019s<\/strong> content and generate weekly statistics from all Social Media platforms<\/li><li>Perform any other tasks that might be assigned in relation to the work scope communications intern&nbsp;<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>If you are the person we are looking for sending us your Curriculum Vitae\/Resume and Cover Letter to <\/strong><a href=\"mailto:info@defyhatenow.org\"><strong>info@defyhatenow.org<\/strong><\/a><strong>&nbsp; before 3rd October 2019.&nbsp;<\/strong><br><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Defy Hate Now is an organization that works on providing data-driven solutions to the problem of hate speech, disinformation, and misinformation in South Sudan and now around Africa. Our work [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":8898,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[3,8,13,14],"tags":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v15.2.1 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ 